{"window": ["2022-02-03T21:40:09.710267+00:00", "2022-09-10T21:04:59.121234+00:00"], "repo_slug": "stephaneyfx/brightness", "candidates": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10", "id": 1322821658, "node_id": "PR_kwDOF0I-6s48WSl_", "number": 10, "title": "Separate blocking and async APIs", "user": {"login": "jacob-pro", "id": 16433349, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2NDMzMzQ5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16433349?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro", "html_url": "https://github.com/jacob-pro", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 9, "created_at": "2022-07-30T00:49:33Z", "updated_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z", "closed_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/pulls/10", "html_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10", "diff_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10.patch", "merged_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z"}, "body": "Hello again :)\r\n\r\nSince my first contributions to this crate and now, I have learnt a lot more about how async Rust works, and I've realised we've made some mistakes I would like to fix...\r\n\r\nAsync functions should not be performing blocking operations. For example if you were building a GUI application, you would expect that when calling an async function it should not be blocking the CPU & event loop whilst waiting for monitors to update. \r\nSee: https://ryhl.io/blog/async-what-is-blocking/\r\n\r\nSo we currently have problems in both:\r\n\r\n- Linux: We are correctly calling the zbus async functions, but incorrecly doing blocking filesystem operations with `std::fs`\r\n- Windows: The whole thing is blocking, since the Win32 C monitor API only provides blocking functions.\r\n\r\nI propose we fix this by having a separate blocking and async API, in the same way that many other crates do such as [reqwest](https://docs.rs/reqwest/latest/reqwest/blocking/index.html) or [zbus](https://docs.rs/zbus/latest/zbus/blocking/index.html).\r\n\r\nHaving a blocking API is also much more convenient / ergonomic for users who are not intending to run within an async context.  \r\n\r\nI recommend running `cargo doc` locally to get a quick overview of the changes!\r\n\r\n(Note: I've tested the Windows side, but not the Linux side as I don't have a suitable device setup at the moment)", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}], "chosen_pr": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10", "id": 1322821658, "node_id": "PR_kwDOF0I-6s48WSl_", "number": 10, "title": "Separate blocking and async APIs", "user": {"login": "jacob-pro", "id": 16433349, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2NDMzMzQ5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16433349?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro", "html_url": "https://github.com/jacob-pro", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 9, "created_at": "2022-07-30T00:49:33Z", "updated_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z", "closed_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/pulls/10", "html_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10", "diff_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10.patch", "merged_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z"}, "body": "Hello again :)\r\n\r\nSince my first contributions to this crate and now, I have learnt a lot more about how async Rust works, and I've realised we've made some mistakes I would like to fix...\r\n\r\nAsync functions should not be performing blocking operations. For example if you were building a GUI application, you would expect that when calling an async function it should not be blocking the CPU & event loop whilst waiting for monitors to update. \r\nSee: https://ryhl.io/blog/async-what-is-blocking/\r\n\r\nSo we currently have problems in both:\r\n\r\n- Linux: We are correctly calling the zbus async functions, but incorrecly doing blocking filesystem operations with `std::fs`\r\n- Windows: The whole thing is blocking, since the Win32 C monitor API only provides blocking functions.\r\n\r\nI propose we fix this by having a separate blocking and async API, in the same way that many other crates do such as [reqwest](https://docs.rs/reqwest/latest/reqwest/blocking/index.html) or [zbus](https://docs.rs/zbus/latest/zbus/blocking/index.html).\r\n\r\nHaving a blocking API is also much more convenient / ergonomic for users who are not intending to run within an async context.  \r\n\r\nI recommend running `cargo doc` locally to get a quick overview of the changes!\r\n\r\n(Note: I've tested the Windows side, but not the Linux side as I don't have a suitable device setup at the moment)", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, "chosen_detail": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/pulls/10", "id": 1012476287, "node_id": "PR_kwDOF0I-6s48WSl_", "html_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10", "diff_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/stephaneyfx/brightness/pull/10.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10", "number": 10, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Separate blocking and async APIs", "user": {"login": "jacob-pro", "id": 16433349, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2NDMzMzQ5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16433349?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro", "html_url": "https://github.com/jacob-pro", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacob-pro/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Hello again :)\r\n\r\nSince my first contributions to this crate and now, I have learnt a lot more about how async Rust works, and I've realised we've made some mistakes I would like to fix...\r\n\r\nAsync functions should not be performing blocking operations. For example if you were building a GUI application, you would expect that when calling an async function it should not be blocking the CPU & event loop whilst waiting for monitors to update. \r\nSee: https://ryhl.io/blog/async-what-is-blocking/\r\n\r\nSo we currently have problems in both:\r\n\r\n- Linux: We are correctly calling the zbus async functions, but incorrecly doing blocking filesystem operations with `std::fs`\r\n- Windows: The whole thing is blocking, since the Win32 C monitor API only provides blocking functions.\r\n\r\nI propose we fix this by having a separate blocking and async API, in the same way that many other crates do such as [reqwest](https://docs.rs/reqwest/latest/reqwest/blocking/index.html) or [zbus](https://docs.rs/zbus/latest/zbus/blocking/index.html).\r\n\r\nHaving a blocking API is also much more convenient / ergonomic for users who are not intending to run within an async context.  \r\n\r\nI recommend running `cargo doc` locally to get a quick overview of the changes!\r\n\r\n(Note: I've tested the Windows side, but not the Linux side as I don't have a suitable device setup at the moment)", "created_at": "2022-07-30T00:49:33Z", "updated_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z", "closed_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z", "merged_at": "2022-09-10T04:07:42Z", "merge_commit_sha": "6b9d67a92940ac5eb810d7a695e47ade71b28266", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/pulls/10/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/pulls/10/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/issues/10/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stephaneyfx/brightness/statuses/6b9d67a92940ac5eb810d7a695e47ade71b28266", "head": {"label": "jacob-pro:master", "ref": "master", "sha": "6b9